perators, functionals and duality, Fourier series, Fourier transform, the fixed point theorem, Baire categories, the uniform bounded principle, the open mapping theorem, the closed graph theorem, the Hahn–Banach theorem, adjoint operators, weak topologies and reflexivity, operators in Hilbert spaces, spectral theory of operators in Hilbert spaces, and compactness. Each chapter ends with workable problems.The book is suitable for graduate students, but also for advanced undergraduates, in mathematics and physics. Contents:List of FiguresBasic NotationChoice PrinciplesHilbert SpacesCompleteness, Completion and DimensionLinear OperatorsFunctionals and Dual SpacesFourier SeriesFourier TransformFixed Point TheoremBaire Category TheoremUniform Boundedness PrincipleOpen Mapping TheoremClosed Graph TheoremHahn–Banach TheoremThe Adjoint OperatorWeak Topologies and ReflexivityOperators in Hilbert SpacesSpectral Theory of Operators on Hilbert SpacesCompactnessBibliographyIndex  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAlgebras, LinearvTextbooks. 0aFunctional analysisvTextbooks. 4aFunktionalanalysis. 7aMATHEMATICS / Functional Analysis.2bisacsh1 aRafeiro, Humberto, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVallejo, Juan Camilo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2016z9783110485288oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831104336470 cprintz978311044191840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044192540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110441925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110441925.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG 